                "id": "5.12.5",
                "title": "Threat Readiness/Information Security Teams",
                "content": "The IS auditor should be aware of the various\ninformation security teams in an organization.\n**Figure 5.63 summarizes the major differences between**\nthese security teams.\n49 EC-Council, \"CEH vs. PenTest+,\" ht1ps://111ww.eccouncil.org/ceh-vs-pentestl\nI 519\n\n\nFigure 5. 63- Comparison of Information Security Teams\n\n# -~\n\n## -\n\n-\n\n# ~\n\n## ~\n\nObjective\nDetect and mitigate\nTest resilience against real\nImprove security posture\ncyberattacks\nattacks\nScope\nOrganizationwide\nOrganizationwide\nPredetermined systems,\nprocesses and employees\nTesting Method\nNo specific methods\nSimulation\nEfficient improvement of security\nemployed\nposture\nTested controls\nNo controls tested\nDetective and responsive\nDetective and preventive\nTools\nEndpoint detection and\nSophisticated, stealthy tools\nSophisticated, stealthy tools and\nresponse (EDR), Security\ndetection software\ninformation and event\nmanagement (SIEM)\nPositioning\nContinuous\nPeriodic\nPeriodic",
